    "In other words, with increasing the degree of TNE, the linear response theory gradually fails and the nonlinear responses begin to become more significant.",
    "The heat flux is no longer only related to the temperature gradient, but also influenced by velocity gradient and/or density gradient.",
    "When the negative contribution from density gradient and/or velocity gradient surpasses the contribution of the temperature gradient, the heat flux will flow from the low-temperature region to the high-temperature region.",
    "The DBM results in this case are confirmed by the DSMC predictions.",
